<subSubSection id="1A320424D2F3E3C647AB93486E1C3E27" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8EF548A77DD861435E8938BF339BE11C" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="619A56D76A654AC0317562723EAE8224" LSID="76D086B0-C653-5478-A6C5-AF5C9C3B1448" authority="Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, new genus record for China" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Mummu" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mummu" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mummu Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, new genus record for China</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EAF726571EF9B5A5461D4E5A6A73E9AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="024CA9AA6497974A6D46699948E1199D" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="A0E306BC924ECC1E219A488AF68B5601" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Mummu" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mummu" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mummu</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, Entomofauna, suppl. 16: 182. Type species (original designation): 
<taxonomicName id="C97CC33F519016213B5771729189E440" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Mummu" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mummu aerata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aerata">Mummu aerata</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009. Type locality N. Vietnam: Lao Cai (Mt. Fan-si-pan W-Seite).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="92962C02372A118383213D714CCA36CE" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="696FD360A8BA39DF6A51F1076DF574D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="419DD67B0C82CE630DC81C6C9BA7A798" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="2A174388AC80001A994742D3EE57DE46" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Mummu" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mummu" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C66CF16EFF6390F55CFDFD136B07F09C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Mummu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also a small, recently erected genus. The obvious diagnostic features are the forewing with dark brown ground colour, a pale distal region along with the outer margin separated by a narrow darker band with a lighter coloured thin and wavy fascia running from the tornus to the costa near the apex. In the male genitalia, the juxta is strongly modified, the presence of a large, finger-shaped, hairy right process of the juxta, and the valvae without saccular processes are two diagnostic features in this genus. The genus presently includes 
<taxonomicName id="D27D533C1DEBB3F09FFC82E2D0020418" genus="M." lsidName="M. aerata" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="aerata">
<emphasis id="01A18E4ECC197E076E1EB67FA538A368" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">M. aerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009 and 
<taxonomicName id="B59D441E600354A604C5FD855DC0E860" genus="M." lsidName="M. cuprea" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="cuprea">
<emphasis id="291B3E114D1F6D62DBCB8236C2230BE0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">M. cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Moore, 1879); the latter was transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="0D75D5E1B463C50C974B6AC054F6C5D9" authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudonirmides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudonirmides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="63E162B2CDAA508D42C542F6E9699130" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Pseudonirmides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Holloway, 1986 (
<bibRefCitation id="2D442C147D8C374E342A9EC4EBDA11B3" author="Hering, M" editor="Seitz, A" journalOrPublisher="Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="665 - 728" refId="B4" refString="Hering, M, 1931. Limacodidae. In: Seitz, A, Ed., Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10. Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart: 665 - 728" title="Limacodidae." volumeTitle="Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10." year="1931">Hering 1931</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="82AFB04026682B8B6A1D45DD876310CF" author="Holloway, JD" journalOrPublisher="Malayan Nature Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 165" refId="B6" refString="Holloway, JD, 1986. The moths of Borneo: Part I. Key to families; families Cossidae, Metarbelidae, Ratardidae, Dudgeoneidae, Epipyropidae and Limacodidae. Malayan Nature Journal 40 (1-2): 1 - 165" title="The moths of Borneo: Part I. Key to families; families Cossidae, Metarbelidae, Ratardidae, Dudgeoneidae, Epipyropidae and Limacodidae." volume="40" year="1986">Holloway 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8E1FFEF75DA0142BE8B3C17B24C2F780" author="Yoshimoto, H" editor="Haruta, T" journalOrPublisher="Tinea Vol. 14 (Supplement 1). The Japan Heterocerists' Society, Tokyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="85 - 89" refId="B29" refString="Yoshimoto, H, 1994. Limacodidae. In: Haruta, T, Ed., Moths of Nepal, Part 3. Tinea Vol. 14 (Supplement 1). The Japan Heterocerists' Society, Tokyo: 85 - 89" title="Limacodidae." volumeTitle="Moths of Nepal, Part 3." year="1994">Yoshimoto 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="71B191CDE710ABC502CD3D77491E1D5A" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B19" refString="Solovyev, AV, Witt, ThJ, 2009. The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33-229." title="The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33 - 229." year="2009">Solovyev and Witt 2009</bibRefCitation>
). We collected four males of 
<taxonomicName id="B2C94DDEF011AFD6C3C32359485401A8" genus="M." lsidName="M. aerata" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="aerata">
<emphasis id="CECCB265CB32217A4CF60D3894B9CBDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">M. aerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southeastern Xizang and southwestern Yunnan; it also indicates that the genus occurs in China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
